    <NOTES>Gold-medal 11C target with Fuller's ESB profile bias. Process-critical checkpoints: (1) oxygenate only once at pitch, (2) start fermentation at 64.4F (18C) and allow controlled rise to 68.0F (20C), (3) run complete diacetyl cleanup before crash, (4) package with strict oxygen control. Water build from RO target: Ca 110, SO4 150, Cl 70, Mg 5, Na 15, HCO3 40 ppm. Suggested salts for total liquor 29 L: gypsum 8.0 g, calcium chloride 4.0 g, epsom 1.0 g; adjust mash pH to 5.30 at room-temp reading. Add invert sugar with 10 min left in boil. Keep post-boil bitterness smooth; avoid aggressive late hopping. Carbonate to 2.0 vols for cask-like balance.</NOTES>
